+# Ari Real Estate - Frontend Deployment Guide
+
+## Overview
+
+This is a React + Vite frontend application for the Ari Real Estate platform. The application provides a professional real estate management interface with admin, authentication, and property listing features.
+
+## Prerequisites
+
+- Node.js 18+ and npm 9+
+- A deployed/running backend instance of AriRealEstate
+- A web hosting platform (Vercel, Netlify, AWS, etc.)
+
+## Environment Configuration
+
+### Development Environment
+
+1. Copy the default configuration:
+```bash
+cp .env.example .env.development
+```
+
+2. For local development with default settings, the app connects to `http://localhost:8080/api`
+
+### Production Environment
+
+Before deploying to production, configure the environment variables:
+
+```bash
+# Create production environment file
+cp .env.example .env.production
+```
+
+Edit `.env.production` and update:
+```
+VITE_API_URL=https://your-backend-domain.com/api
+```
+
+Replace `your-backend-domain.com` with your actual backend URL.
+
+## Installation & Development
+
+```bash
+# Install dependencies
+npm install
+
+# Start development server (runs on http://localhost:5173)
+npm run dev
+
+# Lint code
+npm lint
+
+# Preview production build locally
+npm run preview
+```
+
+## Building for Production
+
+```bash
+# Build optimized production bundle
+npm run build
+
+# Output goes to ./dist directory
+```
+
+The build process automatically:
+- Removes console.log statements
+- Disables source maps
+- Minifies code with Terser
+- Optimizes bundle size
+
+## Deployment Options
+
+### Option 1: Vercel (Recommended)
+
+```bash
+# Install Vercel CLI
+npm i -g vercel
+
+# Deploy
+vercel
+```
+
+Add to `vercel.json`:
+```json
+{
+  "buildCommand": "npm run build",
+  "outputDirectory": "dist",
+  "env": {
+    "VITE_API_URL": "@api_url"
+  }
+}
+```
+
+### Option 2: Netlify
+
+1. Connect your GitHub repository
+2. Build command: `npm run build`
+3. Publish directory: `dist`
+4. Add environment variable in Netlify:
+   - Key: `VITE_API_URL`
+   - Value: `https://your-backend-domain.com/api`
+
+### Option 3: AWS S3 + CloudFront
+
+```bash
+# Build the app
+npm run build
+
+# Sync to S3
+aws s3 sync dist/ s3://your-bucket-name/
+
+# Invalidate CloudFront cache
+aws cloudfront create-invalidation --distribution-id YOUR_DIST_ID --paths "/*"
+```
+
+### Option 4: Traditional Server (Apache, Nginx)
+
+1. Build: `npm run build`
+2. Copy `dist` folder to your server
+3. Configure your web server for SPA routing:
+
+**Nginx:**
+```nginx
+server {
+    listen 80;
+    server_name your-domain.com;
+    root /var/www/ari-frontend/dist;
+    
+    location / {
+        try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html;
+    }
+    
+    location ~* \.(js|css|png|jpg|jpeg|gif|svg|woff|woff2|ttf|eot)$ {
+        expires 30d;
+        add_header Cache-Control "public, immutable";
+    }
+}
+```
+
+**Apache (.htaccess):**
+```apache
+<IfModule mod_rewrite.c>
+  RewriteEngine On
+  RewriteBase /
+  RewriteRule ^index\.html$ - [L]
+  RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f
+  RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-d
+  RewriteRule . /index.html [L]
+</IfModule>
+```
+
+## Backend Configuration
+
+Ensure your backend is configured with proper CORS settings for your frontend domain:
+
+### Backend Environment Variables
+
+```bash
+# In AriRealEstate .env
+CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://your-frontend-domain.com
+FRONTEND_BASE_URL=https://your-frontend-domain.com
+```
+
+### For Development
+
+```bash
+CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:5173
+```
+
+## Security Checklist
+
+- [ ] API URL uses HTTPS in production
+- [ ] Backend CORS is configured for your domain only
+- [ ] Environment variables are set via deployment platform, not committed to git
+- [ ] .env files are in .gitignore (already configured)
+- [ ] Security headers are enabled on backend
+- [ ] JWT secret is strong in production
+- [ ] Database credentials are managed securely
+- [ ] API docs are disabled in production (`API_DOCS_ENABLED=false`)
+
+## Performance Optimization
+
+The build already includes:
+- Code splitting with Vite
+- CSS minification via Vite
+- JavaScript minification via Terser
+- Console log removal in production
+- Source maps disabled for smaller builds
+
+Additional recommendations:
+- Enable gzip compression on your web server
+- Enable browser caching headers
+- Use a CDN for static assets
+- Monitor Core Web Vitals
+
+## Troubleshooting
+
+### "Cannot find module" errors
+- Clear `node_modules`: `rm -rf node_modules && npm install`
+
+### CORS errors
+- Verify `VITE_API_URL` matches backend's `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS`
+- Check backend is running and accessible
+
+### Blank page in production
+- Check browser console for JavaScript errors
+- Verify all routes use HashRouter if not using a server with routing support
+- Ensure `dist` folder is properly deployed
+
+### Environment variables not loading
+- Restart dev server: `npm run dev`
+- Verify `.env` files follow Vite naming: `.env.development`, `.env.production`
+- Variables must start with `VITE_` to be exposed to the app
+
+## Additional Information
+
+- Frontend Framework: React 19+
+- Build Tool: Vite 7+
+- UI Components: Material-UI (MUI)
+- Styling: Tailwind CSS
+- HTTP Client: Axios
+- Routing: React Router v7+
+
+## Support
+
+For issues or questions, refer to:
+- [Vite Documentation](https://vite.dev)
+- [React Documentation](https://react.dev)
+- [Material-UI Documentation](https://mui.com)
